description:
Enable bidirectional linking between Amp threads and Beads issues to support async workflows, notifications, and handoff tracking.

## Context

The ACE framework has three specialized subagents (Generator, Reflector, Curator) that work with Beads issues. Currently there's no link between the Amp threads where work happens and the Beads issues being tracked. This creates a gap in async workflows.

## Use Cases

1. **User creates task in thread** → Bead created → User gets notified when work completes
2. **Generator discovers issues** → Child beads created → Original thread notified
3. **Curator updates knowledge** → Thread that triggered work gets notification
4. **Handoff workflow** → Subagent thread linked to bead → Progress tracked across threads

## Research Required

**CRITICAL**: Before implementation, research Amp codebase using Librarian:
\`\`\`
Librarian query: "How do threads work in https://github.com/sourcegraph/amp/"
Focus on:
- Thread structure and storage (PostgreSQL schema)
- Thread relationships (fork, handoff)
- Environment variables passed to tools (AMP_THREAD_ID)
- Notification mechanisms (polling vs webhooks)
- External API v2 endpoints for thread access
\`\`\`

## Thread Metadata Schema Design

### 1. Bead Extended Metadata

Add to BeadsClient and database schema:

\`\`\`typescript
export interface BeadIssue {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  status: 'open' | 'in_progress' | 'closed';
  priority: number;
  issue_type: 'bug' | 'feature' | 'task' | 'epic' | 'chore';
  created_at: string;
  updated_at: string;
  closed_at?: string;
  labels?: string[];
  assignee?: string;

  // NEW: Amp Thread Integration
  amp_metadata?: AmpThreadMetadata;
}

export interface AmpThreadMetadata {
  // Primary thread that created this bead
  thread_id: string;              // "T-{uuid}"
  thread_url: string;             // "https://ampcode.com/threads/T-{uuid}"
  thread_title?: string;          // Auto-generated or user-set
  workspace_id: string;           // Amp workspace ID

  // Creator context
  created_by_agent?: 'generator' | 'reflector' | 'curator' | 'user';
  created_in_context?: 'main-thread' | 'subagent-thread' | 'handoff';

  // Thread relationships
  main_thread_id?: string;        // If created in subagent thread
  parent_thread_id?: string;      // If created via handoff
  handoff_goal?: string;          // Goal from /handoff command

  // Notification tracking
  last_notified_at?: string;      // ISO 8601 timestamp
  notification_count: number;     // How many notifications sent

  // Sync metadata
  thread_created_at: string;      // ISO 8601 from Amp
  thread_updated_at: string;      // ISO 8601 from Amp
  synced_at: string;              // Last time we checked thread
}
\`\`\`

### 2. Thread-to-Bead Dependency Types

Extend Beads dependency types:

\`\`\`typescript
export type DependencyType = 
  | 'blocks'                      // Task B must complete before task A
  | 'related'                     // Soft connection
  | 'parent-child'                // Epic/subtask
  | 'discovered-from'             // AI discovered during work
  | 'thread-fork'                 // Created from forked thread
  | 'thread-handoff';             // Created from handoff to subagent
\`\`\`

### 3. Notification Event Schema

Define notification payloads:

\`\`\`typescript
export interface BeadNotificationEvent {
  event_id: string;               // UUID for deduplication
  timestamp: string;              // ISO 8601
  bead_id: string;                // ACE_Beads_Amp-X
  thread_id: string;              // Target thread to notify
  event_type: NotificationEventType;
  payload: NotificationPayload;
}

export type NotificationEventType =
  | 'bead_created'                // New bead filed
  | 'bead_completed'              // Bead closed
  | 'bead_blocked'                // Dependency blocking
  | 'knowledge_updated'           // AGENT.md modified
  | 'meta_bead_created'           // Curator created meta bead
  | 'review_needed'               // Human input required
  | 'discovery_chain';            // N discovered issues found

export interface NotificationPayload {
  summary: string;                // One-line description
  details?: {
    bullets_added?: number;
    bullets_updated?: number;
    meta_beads_created?: string[];
    discovered_issues?: string[];
    confidence?: number;
    review_type?: 'conflicting-feedback' | 'low-confidence' | 'consolidation';
  };
  action_required?: boolean;      // Does user need to respond?
  action_url?: string;            // Deep link to specific bead
}
\`\`\`

### 4. Database Extension

Extend Beads SQLite schema:

\`\`\`sql
-- New table for Amp thread metadata
CREATE TABLE amp_thread_metadata (
  bead_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  thread_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  thread_url TEXT NOT NULL,
  thread_title TEXT,
  workspace_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  created_by_agent TEXT,
  created_in_context TEXT,
  main_thread_id TEXT,
  parent_thread_id TEXT,
  handoff_goal TEXT,
  last_notified_at TEXT,
  notification_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  thread_created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  thread_updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  synced_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (bead_id) REFERENCES issues(id)
);

-- Index for finding beads by thread
CREATE INDEX idx_amp_thread_id ON amp_thread_metadata(thread_id);

-- New table for notification queue
CREATE TABLE amp_notifications (
  event_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,
  bead_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  thread_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,
  payload TEXT NOT NULL,           -- JSON
  sent BOOLEAN DEFAULT 0,
  sent_at TEXT,
  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  FOREIGN KEY (bead_id) REFERENCES issues(id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_amp_notifications_unsent ON amp_notifications(sent, timestamp);
CREATE INDEX idx_amp_notifications_thread ON amp_notifications(thread_id);
\`\`\`

## Implementation Approaches

### Approach A: Polling-Based (Recommended First)

**Pros:**
- No Amp server changes needed
- Works with current Amp v2 API
- Simple to implement and test

**Cons:**
- 5-10 second notification delay
- API rate limit concerns
- Polling overhead

**Implementation:**
1. Detect thread context via \`AMP_THREAD_ID\` env var (already passed to tools)
2. Store thread metadata when bead created
3. Background poller checks Amp API for thread updates
4. Write notifications to \`amp_notifications\` table
5. Amp clients poll \`/api/v2/threads\` for updates

### Approach B: MCP Notification Protocol (Future)

**Pros:**
- Real-time notifications
- Standard protocol
- Lower overhead

**Cons:**
- Requires Amp MCP server changes
- Not currently implemented in Amp

**Implementation:**
1. Propose MCP notification support to Amp team
2. Implement \`notifications/message\` handler
3. Beads sends notifications via MCP
4. Amp displays in thread UI

### Approach C: Webhook + Database (Hybrid)

**Pros:**
- Near real-time for critical events
- Batched polling for non-urgent
- Extensible to other integrations

**Cons:**
- More complex architecture
- Requires notification service

**Implementation:**
1. Notification service runs alongside Beads
2. Writes to \`amp_notifications\` table
3. Amp polling service reads table
4. Future: Add webhook receiver to Amp server

## Environment Variable Detection

Tools already receive \`AMP_THREAD_ID\` from Amp:

\`\`\`typescript
// In BeadsClient.createIssue()
const threadContext = {
  thread_id: process.env.AMP_THREAD_ID,
  thread_url: process.env.AMP_THREAD_ID 
    ? \`https://ampcode.com/threads/${process.env.AMP_THREAD_ID}\`
    : undefined,
  workspace_id: process.env.AMP_WORKSPACE_ID,
  created_by_agent: process.env.ACE_ROLE as 'generator' | 'reflector' | 'curator',
};

if (threadContext.thread_id) {
  await beads.createIssue(title, {
    ...options,
    amp_metadata: threadContext
  });
}
\`\`\`

## Notification Delivery Strategies

### Strategy 1: Notification File (Simple)

Write to \`~/.amp/notifications/{workspace-id}.jsonl\`:

\`\`\`typescript
// Amp polls this file every 5 seconds
async function writeNotification(event: BeadNotificationEvent) {
  const file = \`~/.amp/notifications/${event.workspace_id}.jsonl\`;
  await appendFile(file, JSON.stringify(event) + '\n');
}
\`\`\`

### Strategy 2: Amp API Integration (Robust)

Poll Amp's external API:

\`\`\`typescript
async function pollAndNotify() {
  const unsent = await db.query(\`
    SELECT * FROM amp_notifications 
    WHERE sent = 0 
    ORDER BY timestamp ASC 
    LIMIT 100
  \`);

  for (const event of unsent) {
    // Option A: Write to shared database
    await ampDB.insert('notifications', event);

    // Option B: POST to Amp API (if endpoint exists)
    await fetch(\`${AMP_API}/threads/${event.thread_id}/notifications\`, {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify(event)
    });

    await markSent(event.event_id);
  }
}
\`\`\`

### Strategy 3: Client-Side Display (Interim)

Add to Amp thread messages:

\`\`\`typescript
// When user opens thread T-123, check for notifications
const notifications = await beadsAPI.getNotifications({ thread_id: 'T-123' });

// Display as system messages in thread UI
for (const notif of notifications) {
  thread.appendSystemMessage({
    content: notif.payload.summary,
    metadata: { type: 'bead-notification', bead_id: notif.bead_id }
  });
}
\`\`\`

## Handoff Workflow

When user runs \`/handoff ace-generator work on bd-42\`:

\`\`\`typescript
// 1. Amp creates handoff relationship
const relationship = {
  threadID: 'T-new-child',
  type: 'handoff',
  role: 'parent',
  comment: 'work on bd-42',
  createdAt: Date.now()
};
parentThread.relationships.push(relationship);

// 2. Child thread detects handoff context
const childEnv = {
  AMP_THREAD_ID: 'T-new-child',
  AMP_MAIN_THREAD_ID: 'T-parent',
  AMP_HANDOFF_GOAL: 'work on bd-42',
  AMP_WORKSPACE_ID: 'ws-123'
};

// 3. Generator updates bead with handoff metadata
await beads.updateIssue('bd-42', {
  amp_metadata: {
    thread_id: 'T-new-child',
    main_thread_id: 'T-parent',
    parent_thread_id: 'T-parent',
    handoff_goal: 'work on bd-42',
    created_in_context: 'handoff'
  }
});

// 4. Add thread-handoff dependency
await beads.addDependency('bd-42', 'bd-parent', 'thread-handoff');

// 5. Send progress notifications to parent thread
await notifyThread('T-parent', {
  event_type: 'bead_progress',
  summary: 'bd-42 in progress (handoff to ace-generator)'
});
\`\`\`

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] BeadIssue interface extended with amp_metadata field
- [ ] Database schema includes amp_thread_metadata and amp_notifications tables
- [ ] Environment variable detection (\`AMP_THREAD_ID\`) works in all subagents
- [ ] Thread metadata captured when beads created in thread context
- [ ] Handoff relationships tracked via thread-handoff dependency type
- [ ] Notification events written to amp_notifications table
- [ ] At least one notification delivery strategy implemented (recommend file-based first)
- [ ] Test scenario: create bead in thread → complete → verify notification
- [ ] Test scenario: handoff workflow → bead linked to child thread → parent notified
- [ ] Documentation for thread-to-bead workflow

